recipes.title: Scrambled Eggs with Toast
recipes.description: A quick and easy breakfast dish made with fluffy scrambled eggs served with crispy toast.
instructions: Crack the eggs into a bowl and whisk with milk, salt, and pepper.
Heat a pan over medium heat and add butter.
Pour in the egg mixture and gently stir until eggs are just set.
Toast the bread slices until golden brown.
Serve scrambled eggs over or beside the toast.

recipes.title: Banana Pancakes
recipes.description: Fluffy pancakes made with ripe bananas, perfect for a healthy and delicious breakfast.
instructions: Mash the bananas in a bowl.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, sugar, and milk. Mix well.
Heat a skillet over medium heat and add a little butter or oil.
Pour batter into small circles and cook until bubbles form.
Flip and cook the other side until golden brown.
Serve with syrup, honey, or fresh fruit.

recipes.title: Avocado Toast with Poached Egg
recipes.description: A trendy and healthy breakfast featuring creamy avocado spread on crispy toast, topped
instructions: Toast the bread slices until golden.
Mash the avocado with a pinch of salt and pepper.
Bring a small pot of water to a simmer, add vinegar.
Crack each egg into a small bowl, gently pour into water, and poach for 34 minutes.
Spread mashed avocado on toast.
Top with poached egg and sprinkle chili flakes if desired.

recipes.title: Spicy Tomato Basil Penne
recipes.description: A bold red pasta dish made with zesty tomato sauce, fresh basil, and a touch of chili for heat. It's vibrant, flavorful, and satisfying.
ingredients: 1 tsp red chili flakes (adjust to taste)
instructions: Cook penne in salted boiling water until al dente. Drain and set aside.
In a large pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add garlic and onion, saut until soft.
Stir in chili flakes and cook for 30 seconds.
Add crushed tomatoes, salt, pepper, and sugar if using. Simmer uncovered for 1015 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked pasta to the sauce and toss to coat evenly.
Stir in fresh basil, and garnish with Parmesan before serving.
